      • moveRobber

        public void moveRobber(VertexObject position)
                throws GameMapException
        Moves the robber to a different position on the map
        Parameters:
        position, - the VertextObject where the robber will be placed
        Throws:
        GameMapException - if this function runs and dies when it shoouldn't
        Precondition
        The current player must have rolled a 7;
        Postcondition
        The robber will be moved to a different position on the map

      • placeSettlement

        public void placeSettlement(VertexObject position)
                     throws GameMapException
        Places a settlement for the player on a given vertex
        Parameters:
        position, - (vertex): the vertex where the player wants to place the settlement
        Throws:
        GameMapException - if this function runs and dies when it shoouldn't
        Precondition
        The player has to have the resources (1 wheat, 1 brick, 1 lumber, 1 sheep) for a settlement and the vertex has to be connected to a player's road and at least 2 edges away from another settlement or city. And the player has a settlement left.
        Postcondition
        A settlement will be placed at the desired vertex

      • placeCity

        public void placeCity(VertexObject position)
               throws GameMapException
        Places a city for the player on a given vertex
        Parameters:
        position, - (vertex): the vertex where the player wants to place the city
        Throws:
        GameMapException - if this function runs and dies when it shoouldn't
        Precondition
        The player must have the resources (2 wheat, 3 ore) for a city and the vertex must be connected to a player's road and at least 2 edges away from another settlement or city. And the player has a city left.
        Postcondition
        a city will be placed at the desired vertex

      • placeRoad

        public void placeRoad(VertexObject position)
               throws GameMapException
        Places a road for the player on a given edge
        Parameters:
        position, - (edge): the edge where the player wants to place a road
        Throws:
        GameMapException - if this function runs and dies when it shoouldn't
        Precondition
        The player must have the resources (1 lumber, 1 brick) for a road and the edge must be connected to a player's road or municipality and the edge must not be occupied by another piece. And the player has a road left.
        Postcondition
        a road will be placed at the desired edge
